DaynaPORT SCSI/Link Linux 2.0 driver -- change history

0.5  2026-06-16
      - RX: poll continuously while frames are arriving -- re-issue the next
        READ(6) immediately (via the immediate task queue) instead of waiting a
        poll interval, falling back to the timer only once a READ comes back
        empty.
      - New debug module parameter (off by default): logs per-READ RX yield and
        rate every 256 READs, to characterize the bottleneck on a given HBA/CPU.

0.4  2026-06-13
      - Refactored shared code into lib/

0.3  2026-06-11
      - RX poll cadence is now tunable via bare module parameters (milliseconds),
        so it can be swept at load time without rebuilding:
          insmod scsilink.o poll_ms=80 poll0_ms=20 fast_hold=16
        Defaults reproduce v0.2 timing and seem approximately optimal for a 486@33Mhz
        based on real-world testing with a BlueSCSI v2
      - RX: drop the unused device flag-field handling; record parsing relies on
        the zero-length terminator alone.

0.2  2026-06-09
     - RX: batch up to 2 frames per READ(6) (SCSILINK_RX_REQ 1524 -> 4096),
       ~75% speed increase.

0.1  2026-06-09
     Initial release.
     - Builds as a loadable module against any configured Linux 2.0.x kernel
